@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Dungeon Petz Pet Cage Reference";
}

<style>
#pet-table .table-row {
    padding-top: 3em;
}

#pet-table ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
}
</style>


<h3>Special Pets</h3>

<div id="pet-table" class="table table-100">
    <div class="table-row" style="padding-top: 0;">
        <div class="table-cell tc-1">
            <img src="~/lib/Images/DungeonPetz/Piggy.png" style="" />
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-2">
            Sly Piggy
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-8">
            Each <b>satisfied</b> play need: may move 1 manure to neighboring cage/plot
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-1">
            <img src="~/lib/Images/DungeonPetz/Pearlpusher.png" style="" />
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-2">
            Pearlpusher
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-8">
            <ul>
                <li>After adding 1<sup>+</sup> manure, put a gold token on <b>one</b></li>
                <li>Keep gold if it is cleaned</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-1">
            <img src="~/lib/Images/DungeonPetz/Nomnivore.png" style="" />
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-2">
            Nomnivore
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-8">
            Eats all items depicted
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-1">
            <img src="~/lib/Images/DungeonPetz/Vampire.png" style="" />
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-2">
            House Vampire
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-8">
            <ul>
                <li>Hunger needs beyond 1 require an imp</li>
                <li>Send imp to hospital (armor doesn't block)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-1">
            <img src="~/lib/Images/DungeonPetz/Spook.png" style="" />
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-2">
            Shining Spook
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-8">
            <ul>
                <li>When adding mutation, may give it to neighboring pet instead</li>
                <li>Max 1 mutation per pet per round (i.e. max 2)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-1">
            <img src="~/lib/Images/DungeonPetz/Lemur.png" style="" />
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-2">
            Soulful-Eyed Lemur
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-8">
            <ul>
                <li>Each pair of like needs <b>assigned</b> to a neighbor satisfies one of that need</li>
                <li>Can benefit from both neighbors</li>
                <li>A pair must come from same neighbor</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-1">
            <img src="~/lib/Images/DungeonPetz/Sickie.png" style="" />
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-2">
            Snuggly Sickie
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-8">
            <ul>
                <li>0 disease: treat as 1 disease</li>
                <li>Else: treat as 0 disease</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-1">
            <img src="~/lib/Images/DungeonPetz/Pony.png" style="" />
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-2">
            Pony
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-8">
            <ul>
                <li>Each excess anger need: satisfy 1 play need for <b>all other</b> cages</li>
                <li>Applies whether or not she escapes</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-1">
            <img src="~/lib/Images/DungeonPetz/Wreckie.png" style="" />
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-2">
            Wreckie
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-8">
            <ul>
                <li>Each excess anger need: remove one cage or addon</li>
                <li>Contained by destroying things, rather than imps</li>
                <li>Other pets will not run away (until phase 3)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-1">
            <img src="~/lib/Images/DungeonPetz/Yummy.png" style="width: 60px" />
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-2">
            Yummy
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-8">
            <ul>
                <li>Eats only meat or vegetables, depending on turn</li>
                <li>Choose color before drawing cards by placing one facedown</li>
                <li>Facedown card cannot be used this round</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-1">
            <img src="~/lib/Images/DungeonPetz/Skelly.png" style="width: 60px" />
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-2">
            Skelly
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-8">
            <ul>
                <li>Never eats, any hunger need (even from potion) adds suffering</li>
                <li>Take a potion when acquiring</li>
                <li>Each potion: choose a need to apply for exhibitions & sales</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

